Federal funds sold amounted to $15.8 million at December 31, 2017 as compared to $2.4 million at December 31, 2016. These funds represent excess daily liquidity which is invested on an unsecured basis with well capitalized banks, in amounts generally limited both in the aggregate and to any one bank.
